cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.CE, cs.NI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with secure communication over a wiretap channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). It also involves the use of non-linear operations in the eavesdropper's receiver, which is related to circuit design and electronics (cs.CE) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). Finally, the paper evaluates achievable secrecy rates, which could involve mathematical modeling and simulation (cs.MM).
